  "cooked": "<p>The BIP is now no longer in draft state and there is a Bitcoin Core implementation as well:\n</p><aside class=\"onebox githubpullrequest\" data-onebox-src=\"https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/29050\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n\n      <a href=\"https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/29050\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin</a>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    <div class=\"github-row\">\n\n\n\n    <div class=\"github-icon-container\" title=\"Pull Request\">\n      <svg width=\"60\" height=\"60\" class=\"github-icon\" viewBox=\"0 0 12 16\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M11 11.28V5c-.03-.78-.34-1.47-.94-2.06C9.46 2.35 8.78 2.03 8 2H7V0L4 3l3 3V4h1c.27.02.48.11.69.31.21.2.3.42.31.69v6.28A1.993 1.993 0 0 0 10 15a1.993 1.993 0 0 0 1-3.72zm-1 2.92c-.66 0-1.2-.55-1.2-1.2 0-.65.55-1.2 1.2-1.2.65 0 1.2.55 1.2 1.2 0 .65-.55 1.2-1.2 1.2zM4 3c0-1.11-.89-2-2-2a1.993 1.993 0 0 0-1 3.72v6.56A1.993 1.993 0 0 0 2 15a1.993 1.993 0 0 0 1-3.72V4.72c.59-.34 1-.98 1-1.72zm-.8 10c0 .66-.55 1.2-1.2 1.2-.65 0-1.2-.55-1.2-1.2 0-.65.55-1.2 1.2-1.2.65 0 1.2.55 1.2 1.2zM2 4.2C1.34 4.2.8 3.65.8 3c0-.65.55-1.2 1.2-1.2.65 0 1.2.55 1.2 1.2 0 .65-.55 1.2-1.2 1.2z\"></path></svg>\n    </div>\n\n  <div class=\"github-info-container\">\n\n\n\n      <h4>\n        <a href=\"https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/29050\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Add OP_TXHASH and OP_CHECKTXHASHVERIFY opcodes</a>\n      </h4>\n\n    <div class=\"branches\">\n      <code>bitcoin:master</code> \u2190 <code>stevenroose:txhash</code>\n    </div>\n\n      <div class=\"github-info\">\n        <div class=\"date\">\n          opened <span class=\"discourse-local-date\" data-format=\"ll\" data-date=\"2023-12-11\" data-time=\"09:00:40\" data-timezone=\"UTC\">09:00AM - 11 Dec 23 UTC</span>\n        </div>\n\n        <div class=\"user\">\n          <a href=\"https://github.com/stevenroose\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">\n            <img alt=\"stevenroose\" src=\"https://delvingbitcoin.org/uploads/default/original/1X/265a2a0431c002e72d5c3f3cc33dbbd318ef911d.jpeg\" class=\"onebox-avatar-inline\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" data-dominant-color=\"CCBAA8\">\n            stevenroose\n          </a>\n        </div>\n\n        <div class=\"lines\" title=\"10 commits changed 30 files with 2942 additions and 19 deletions\">\n          <a href=\"https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/29050/files\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">\n            <span class=\"added\">+2942</span>\n            <span class=\"removed\">-19</span>\n          </a>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n  <div class=\"github-row\">\n    <p class=\"github-body-container\">Implementation of OP_TXHASH and OP_CHECKTXHASHVERIFY, as per the [draft BIP](htt<span class=\"show-more-container\"><a href=\"https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/29050\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\" class=\"show-more\">\u2026</a></span><span class=\"excerpt hidden\">ps://github.com/bitcoin/bips/pull/1500).\n\nThis MR includes a test using the test vectors generated from the reference implementation in the BIP.\nThe implementation utilizes a caching strategy that hopefully alleviates concerns around resource usage like quadratic hashing.\n\n(I'm not very familiar with checks and lints on here, so I'll try to address problems as they come. I have personally been able to compile and run the tests, but that usually is only the tip of the iceberg.)</span></p>\n  </div>\n\n  </article>\n\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"clear: both\"></div>\n</aside>\n",
